{"type":"message","id":"78b23578","parentId":"29424099","timestamp":"2026-04-16T15:24:16.676Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Crafting a formal tasking map**\n\nI need to design a formal tasking map with conceptual sections like mission, primary outcomes, non-goals, system roles, workstreams, capability layers, operating modes, the admin assistant role, and phased scope. The user wants my perspective on this. I found two relevant Apollo documents that reinforce a local-first modular approach; I'll sharpen that up. I should also note that while I can assist with medical regimen, I can't replace a clinician—emphasizing the importance of human approval. Strong structure will be key!\n\n**Defining Apollo's tasks**\n\nI think I should outline that Apollo should be assigned to three classes of work: knowledge work, operations work, and program work. My goal is to keep the explanation concise yet detailed enough to cover each area effectively. By breaking it down this way, I can ensure clarity while showing how Apollo will operate in these different capacities. It’s essential that the user has a clear understanding of these classifications and their implications. Let’s produce this as requested!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_0143781879c152dd0169e0fef46cd88191b96a2cda5a411501\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp4P77trEWovct1M76YvV5R08ZDpCm6CbuyCXuYl_9fc8t4OngnFHZ__7dm5TI5sZk1pUHuHfmf5TeRBBXlX2PHNEMP0VRqbMYaTFPegdZHykQK4iQKex_jUja4yOr9QFgLiFtPj3yn4J5st2WiIpuU664vyuTVEdvMR7wmNKPrmzB_YZwwqHHROZEhdoJbTFb7_yQs69fqyqRjIvwTEvdzXJvlNc_YfqQDOTKN6auwtjebhqTvqGx0pp313aPhz-EdafAPQH7X0QTvNaf_KfrXkultMKrYPVoj2Kdy9qnHNf9IIWBJu9iUz56tPOx743XgzFhExXgxdytVdyow9CYoT9jWUg_hzACIjDPgI6D_K_l0HqiZtsUtKsx-I1TxAMSgj7MaJSXLDsRKY0V_4D_KvxMVnSCTPjHQpphHBpUB_7CUneMUGLQsykg4Wv8UNym2XRLno7-VVMofLYZFQlpfLeJqC67IQcnMehaEcbwykXYU3Qdo3U_3VcsFiH5zDZM8BjH7eZ_WiiXPhOw7K2t6Uzle87qkMd0KTQ888_OmdkofUs5cwbLnugYCd3Rb1e6R99KGQwrcKZi_bLPbPXY5g-lt1D5kM