{"type":"message","id":"c2ed4dee","parentId":"e0a2823a","timestamp":"2026-04-16T16:57:37.821Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_COsDO3GiyIXRBhSP9QKRaYY1|fc_0143781879c152dd0169e115022e308191a44c791cd04d75fd","toolName":"memory_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"f6ec02d39ca28dee70abf949a7d31fc46179b57fa7817d9e1a9642d07e2632d5\",\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 191,\n      \"endLine\": 255,\n      \"score\": 0.6077364961959049,\n      \"textScore\": 0.6077364961959049,\n      \"snippet\": \"4. **Operational document generation**\\n   For each project, generate:\\n   - `timeline.md`\\n   - `master_context.md`\\n   - `decisions.md`\\n   - `tasks.md`\\n   - `deliverables.md`\\n\\n5. **Clean ingestion set for LightRAG**\\n   - ingest both:\\n     - source documents\\n     - distilled project docs\\n   - this gives better recall plus better synthesis\\n\\n6. **Then grow into phase 3**\\n   - agent tasking\\n   - monitoring\\n   - UI/workflow orchestration\\n   - project-aware mission prompts\\n\\n**What I would do next, concretely**\\n1. build the **manifest + dedupe report**\\n2. create **project folders** under `vault/Clean/projects/`\\n3. classify the raw docs into **Apollo / Aurelius / Other**\\n4. generate the first two proj\\n\\nSource: memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md#L191-L255\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md#L191-L255\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"c8b55d23b329dce2ab03bb1ad826ba415711770f477bec9482fbcd5f9dac0aa8\",\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 154,\n      \"endLine\": 204,\n      \"score\": 0.6035164837111274,\n      \"textScore\": 0.6035164837111274,\n      \"snippet\": \"What are our next steps?\\nassistant: I’m going to quickly inspect the raw corpus so the next steps are grounded in what’s actually there, not hand-wavy.\\nassistant: Yes, this is very workable. I checked the corpus, and it’s substantial for a person but still modest for a machine.\\n\\nWhat’s in `vault/raw` now:\\n- **69 files**\\n- about **11.7 MB** total\\n- mostly `.txt` research exports\\n- plus:\\n  - `MyActivity.html`\\n  - one `.pdf`\\n  - one `.xlsx`\\n- there are clear duplicates and near-duplicates\\n- there are clearly multiple project families, at least **Apollo** and **Aurelius**\\n\\nSo the next steps should be practical and staged.\\n\\n**Recommended pipeline, phase 2: robust project ingestion**\\n\\n1. **Invento\\n\\nSource: memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md#L154-L204\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md#L154-L204\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"9eb6e27b031bc55cfe5d6542039c58327f403b37a1ae347415a275942ab7cd59\",\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 79,\n      \"endLine\": 105,\n      \"score\": 0.3666523939484407,\n      \"textScore\": 0.3666523939484407,\n      \"snippet\": \"Amplification: each project is divided into several conversations due to thread length limitations and convenience. are we able to concatenate them in our processing?\\nThe point being that once we have this data available we should be able to:\\n- generate precise and concise mission tasking\\n- orchestrate agents to provide generation, monitoring and user interface with said projects.\\n\\nIn other words I would like to get to the point where you (or another llm instance) is able to have a conversation with me about the contents of our previous discussions seamlessly and be able to comprehensively but clearly and disctinctly enumerate project tasking, steps and deliverables.\\n\\nIs that an achievable g\\n\\nSource: memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md#L79-L105\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md#L79-L105\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"b0bfc99db674b46e4091a064ab13d2a31eeff7b9d32b5a5d592b5804cc6ab8a1\",\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 54,\n      \"endLine\": 83,\n      \"score\": 0.3027521923021173,\n      \"textScore\": 0.3027521923021173,\n      \"snippet\": \"- if you ingest the full raw dump now, you may pollute the library with junk and duplicated concepts\\n\\nSo yes, you *can* ingest directly from the current clean markdown, but I think the better path is:\\n- **not** from the original raw HTML-derived dump\\n- **yes** from a **filtered and possibly split** markdown set\\n\\nBest option:\\n- create an **Apollo-only filtered corpus**\\n- split by conversation entry or by theme\\n- place those files into the LightRAG input location\\n\\nIf you want, I can do this next:\\n1. create `vault/Clean/apollo_only.md`\\n2. or create `vault/Clean/apollo_topics/` with many smaller `.md` files\\n\\nI recommend **2**.\\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"label\\\": \\\"openclaw-con\\n\\nSource: memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md#L54-L83\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md#L54-L83\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"d661d6b19000d7e3950eb0bf14147671313e956bc9961567b38f07310a72aa37\",\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 97,\n      \"endLine\": 135,\n      \"score\": 0.29830010147249836,\n      \"textScore\": 0.29830010147249836,\n      \"snippet\": \"6. **generate project summaries, task lists, decisions, and deliverables**\\n7. ingest both the **source docs** and the **derived summaries** into LightRAG\\n\\nThat gives you two layers:\\n- **raw evidence layer**: exact conversation excerpts\\n- **operational layer**: distilled project memory, tasks, constraints, decisions\\n\\nThat second layer is what will make future conversations feel seamless.\\n\\nSo the target state is very realistic:\\n- you ask about Apollo or Aurelius\\n- the system recalls prior decisions and context\\n- it distinguishes projects clearly\\n- it can produce mission tasking, next steps, risks, and deliverables\\n- agents can then act from that structured context\\n\\nWhat I’d recommend building:\\n\\nSource: memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md#L97-L135\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md#L97-L135\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"provider\": \"none\",\n  \"citations\": \"auto\",\n  \"mode\": \"fts-only\"\n}"}],"details":{"results":[{"id":"f6ec02d39ca28dee70abf949a7d31fc46179b57fa7817d9e1a9642d07e2632d5","path":"memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md","startLine":191,"endLine":255,"score":0.6077364961959049,"textScore":0.6077364961959049,"snippet":"4. **Operational document generation**\n   For each project, generate:\n   - `timeline.md`\n   - `master_context.md`\n   - `decisions.md`\n   - `tasks.md`\n   - `deliverables.md`\n\n5. **Clean ingestion set for LightRAG**\n   - ingest both:\n     - source documents\n     - distilled project docs\n   - this gives better recall plus better synthesis\n\n6. **Then grow into phase 3**\n   - agent tasking\n   - monitoring\n   - UI/workflow orchestration\n   - project-aware mission prompts\n\n**What I would do next, concretely**\n1. build the **manifest + dedupe report**\n2. create **project folders** under `vault/Clean/projects/`\n3. classify the raw docs into **Apollo / Aurelius / Other**\n4. generate the first two proj\n\nSource: memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md#L191-L255","source":"memory","citation":"memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md#L191-L255"},{"id":"c8b55d23b329dce2ab03bb1ad826ba415711770f477bec9482fbcd5f9dac0aa8","path":"memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md","startLine":154,"endLine":204,"score":0.6035164837111274,"textScore":0.6035164837111274,"snippet":"What are our next steps?\nassistant: I’m going to quickly inspect the raw corpus so the next steps are grounded in what’s actually there, not hand-wavy.\na