If I use `docker compose up -d --force-recreate apollo-agent` after making changes, it'll ensure the existing container recognizes the new bind mounts only after it's recreated.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Discussing live workspace modification**\\n\\nI can modify the workspace files live through the OpenClaw interface since they are bind-mounted. If the user simply wants to add files to C:/Apollo/Intel/workspace or the Vault on the host, there's no need for a restart. It might be best to keep things under the existing mounts for simplicity. I could suggest creating a subfolder within C:/Apollo/Intel/workspace/project or under the Vault to keep everything organized.\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"You probably **do not need to shut everything down**, unless you want to change what paths are mounted.\n\n## Short answer\n\n### If the files are going inside paths already mounted:\n- `C:/Apollo/Intel/workspace`\n- `C:/Apollo/Vault`\n- or anywhere under `C:/Apollo/Intel` visible via `/home/node/.openclaw`\n\nthen **no compose change is needed** and **no restart is needed**.  \nYou can modify them directly from the host, and I can read them immediately.\n\n### If you want OpenClaw to see a new folder outside those mounts:\nthen **yes**, you need to:\n1. edit `docker-compose.yaml`\n2. add the new bind mount\n3. recreate the relevant container(s)\n\nBut you do **not** need a full stack shutdown. Usually just recreating `apollo-agent` is enough, and maybe `open-webui` too if you want that container to see the same files.\n\n## Based on your current compose\n\nYou already have:\n\n- `C:/Apollo/Intel:/home/node/.openclaw`\n- `C:/Apollo/Intel/workspace:/home/node/.openclaw/workspace`\n- `C:/Apollo/Vault:/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/vault`\n\nSo if you place the project material under:\n- `C:/Apollo/Intel/workspace/...`\n- or `C:/Apollo/Vault/...`\n\nI should be able to use it without any container changes.\n\n## Practical recommendation\n\nSimplest path:\n- put the project folder under `C:/Apollo/Intel/workspace/`\n- or under `C:/Apollo/Vault/`\n- then tell me where it is\n\nNo restart, no compose edit, no risk to the running conversation.\n\nIf you want, once you’ve placed it there, I can inspect the tree and tell you exactly what is already usable and what should become the first setup tasks.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0143781879c152dd0169e13ed562d88191b4d55acfb3d18052\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":925,"output":916,"cacheRead":39936,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41777,"cost":{"input":0.0023125000000000003,"output":0.01374,"cacheRead":0.009984,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0260365}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776369349334,"responseId":"resp_0143781879c152dd0169e13ec6199c8191b313e887c8619f98"}}
