{"type":"message","id":"98c8acff","parentId":"8252c00a","timestamp":"2026-04-16T20:17:36.181Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Crafting final feedback**\n\nI need to create a concise summary that clearly mentions what was moved and what was left behind, along with the reasons. It might be helpful to include a PowerShell command for the user to use if they want to manage any leftover items. I should also note the permissions issues encountered while running the container context. Additionally, it's important to specify that nothing was deleted and perhaps include the legacy report path as well as exact paths. Let's put this all together!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_0143781879c152dd0169e143d4adc08191b2047495e3509b5c\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp4UPYP6IKnaF7MU6jI1elkYE3lF_w-GmqpKImkHBGx2qLYDvEwl8221Pb56VsqwE2KfFkwE9NbqeFKKbUAljDmIrk3BW5SD168Qz5uphJ00q_3VqWZGz984STVPd4w88UJcN6Jl7ZQHdu2dktdF2WCYQ-0CFWUIEWZkvC9ecchFRfJ0tYHAZRGEWf8IdFwBRt0LPfaAlQjlhzq0Un_V4V2Z4UJvKcyimNcWhMBBxtKt4NVNocF9Xu-12I6meCCPg9fwZ2E5JkZxFjP1c9ccF448W71XADPJjIY1_SAALYhafEhTtg2XPhcRnbSY9yJP0ui0B5hiJnoLYqi8oVOOkvsy9Ab-cdv1tF2RgjBm1Bxd_IjhfKsneSqiF3m8rq8LW8rQhbDZXL_g5Y-fMkgkukLeSFm0J9UhNPJvDSyVy5IDzxuv_Of-xikRQO5PNecqKbqEfkATC3pXZ_wMTTcI2M9JGEy-09swkehlXxbnQBktN7TLUA6rx4brKasZXOLPIesW9wfMLzXVZ8mwfNEQa5VnAbCO2I_q9Em52uSZ_noKT6C3G7bxqLh67Gec24sUvqn8eGgv04ltzaS5JoJNUCPFG10Ohz15ljwCRyo84IJWB6NwbuQOwWa17HcDNimmqdVyg8IeiNuxMuXGw-KCbwf2iqRR71mSjfiIC_v9chs_YY_jt2rEGy53asuB6EeIZzLPQZQOw5YPqwg3KKifzEMqcqBQqbyTdf9itgHjY0fKG4wh3RhPQ-NA6vKpUdNov4yLJ0Xi_8TKWkW7aZSmnfVptwHsZcly4SyeKym3ljoFScBAG05ULIll-bmgJpvxdHcfduAw5-9icApSMq5xRt6Fu__507XoeJnqIXOzMjlL2nCib44_L0GhlZSFguD84XxjItqc9J4_uikPs1j1_9CwB6VGJSX3hnssi0i4gOBfxm7M2N0Mlz0QRVUByX5Uz_vp1dQFKuB-N5V2CL220pqy2udkimrg-oO0mNqNkn__s3Y-sroADKJvIAuJTer3kXiTdQYIscgfYrwEKVT-i7AVKzcJK4cMW3MyPXhchCka_ilye2WKR9eKbJ8Bi39P5fs4pt8z7Wq1AjUvzd-FO7fdO3aZJVo2N6R4toEk-H8Y1614oLaVMA6g1vx8e3YWrSBLOdSh0DgSgf_iwisWM6vCRH6rAV5P1NDElbu8JweGSAEsmyYeo_j6pdxbvhj0lnR0ruWDuYHBDoiNOpmmHBl1YdBniOvc-YidSDBwR04cH7svs3eHhqxmacoS5XDQqbZuWAlmscX3JDwJq0TMiI8dCRnZrxgzpbYCWpSMMYY8xBhBiaHCW4FlBdalYomkhhuZ-ybYpf_-s7-oCMtroFsu4qm8pm7LaGq8Ocls8-ksVy8sZ3kME0RqyKj-0oTF3_iuMFgthDsuEhHxFzMnbWoePIiivtiErznzfFI-5ZpDjm1xugunj_L-Q-SWe4c1zkpCYo_CFWo4RHj-_IMJ5QpGyaWpBAxiHOE4yT7Uh3K7hafHbZz2VULSgiH8Z_hrRhSEi8YMPrht_591siiqD4ewGlnPyAqhRcJEKBWA-cxhhlij33qncMtGByxR5iGTxHfKcA\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Crafting final feedback**\\n\\nI need to create a concise summary that clearly mentions what was moved and what was left behind, along with the reasons. It might be helpful to include a PowerShell command for the user to use if they want to manage any leftover items. I should also note the permissions issues encountered while running the container context. Additionally, it's important to specify that nothing was deleted and perhaps include the legacy report path as well as exact paths. Let's put this all together!\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"Done, mostly cleanly.\n\n## What I archived\nI moved the clearly legacy **old nested workspace content** from:\n\n- `Intel/workspace/...`\n\ninto a reversible mirror at:\n\n- `legacy/Intel/workspace/...`\n\n### Moved successfully\n- `AGENTS.md`\n- `BOOTSTRAP.md`\n- `HEARTBEAT.md`\n- `IDENTITY.md`\n- `SOUL.md`\n- `TOOLS.md`\n- `USER.md`\n- `memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md`\n- `state/`\n\nSo the old duplicate workspace guidance and old session memory are now out of the way, but still trivially recoverable.\n\n## What I deliberately left alone\nI did **not** touch active-looking OpenClaw runtime/config state under `Intel/`, including:\n- `openclaw.json*`\n- `memory/`\n- `memory.md`\n- `tasks/`\n- `flows/`\n- `logs/`\n- `devices/`\n- `identity/`\n- `subagents/`\n- `exec-approvals.json`\n\nThat was the safe choice.\n\n## What remains in `Intel/workspace`\nThree leftovers are still there:\n\n- `Intel/workspace/.git/`\n- `Intel/workspace/.openclaw/`\n- `Intel/workspace/vault/`\n\nThese did **not** move because of ownership/runtime permission friction from the current container context, not because they look important.\n\nNotes:\n- `vault/` appears empty\n- `.openclaw/` is tiny\n- `.git/` is the main leftover\n\n## Report written\nI wrote a record here:\n\n- `legacy/archive-report-2026-04-16.md`\n\n## My assessment\nThis was a good cleanup. The major duplicate clutter is now archived, and the current repo root is much less confusing.\n\nAlso, your recent ingestion/digestion work in `Vault/Clean/` looks useful, so I left it untouched.\n\n## If you want the cleanup fully finished\nYou should run a host-side move for those three remaining leftovers, since I can’t elevate from this session.\n\n### PowerShell\n```powershell\nNew-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path C:\\Apollo\\legacy\\Intel\\workspace | Out-Null\n\nMove-Item -Force C:\\Apollo\\Intel\\workspace\\.git       C:\\Apollo\\legacy\\Intel\\workspace\\\nMove-Item -Force C:\\Apollo\\Intel\\workspace\\.openclaw C:\\Apollo\\legacy\\Intel\\workspace\\\nMove-Item -Force C:\\Apollo\\Intel\\workspace\\vault      C:\\Apollo\\legacy\\Intel\\workspace\\\n```\n\nIf you want, next I’d inspect the existing `Vault/Clean/projects/*` and `ingest_manifest.json` so we can decide exactly what to wire into Apollo first.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0143781879c152dd0169e143d8d5688191b1b661f04d48c1dc\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":212,"output":685,"cacheRead":64896,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65793,"cost":{"input":0.0005300000000000001,"output":0.010275,"cacheRead":0.016224,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.027028999999999997}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776370643355,"responseId":"resp_0143781879c152dd0169e143d401d88191830f1a15d8ba6e94"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e7d23d6e","parentId":"98c8acff","timestamp":"2026-04-16T20:25:17.656Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Thu 2026-04-16 20:25 UTC] ok.. cleanup fully finished now. how would we go about making a persistent track of this project's purpose, status, deliverables and steps checklist in order to maintain consitency? can we put an md file or json somewhere? possibly even inside our database?"}],"timestamp":1776371117651}}
{"type":"message","id":"a95740f2","parentId":"e7d23d6e","timestamp":"2026-04-16T20:25:47.784Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Evaluating project structure**\n\nI’m thinking about whether to create `projects/apollo/` or use an existing path like `Vault/Clean/projects/apollo`. This existing path already has master context, timelines, tasks, and deliverables. I believe the best approach is to keep this as versioned files for easy access instead of hiding them in a database. I’ll suggest using markdown for documents like `charter.md`, `status.md`, and others, while considering reusing existing files to avoid duplication. Maybe syncing with `Vault/Clean/projects/apollo` would also work.\n\n**Considering documentation options**\n\nI’m thinking about how to address the user’s question regarding dashboards and queries later, while emphasizing that markdown in git is the best single source of truth for now. I might need to update my plan, but I want to be clear and not give a simple answer. I could offer to set it up, even though they haven't explicitly asked for it yet. It feels like a good idea to be proactive and suggest creating it right away!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_0143781879c152dd0169e145af7ccc81918a760eebc8f8f675\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp4UW75SSkWHGaR7kJaD25EOS7Qb3Nkf1lwEu0iqPGYCfu0PY6yYw1G5V2il6Bu6dMWM69Kc4tVoCRfTskEOzlgguxUm4P96a2hyMq7h5UKDzG4KABcpWmkYtqTknuBcjigS81WBBPqigA0erl_RXmaDc1kVDGawb1GGLZ7dFMFniO_Psw3lvDCoTY52QMOK2LIQMDN5St-k5-eOUe2qvILJL4AH9OFgj0KWGjhAGGrAxlYyze5sel9TJHlWw-SstW2CS3Q0rz8c-JPHmYG1yYoiejd9YtMUWQk0Z0DPr0lu_Y3DtKwyPrAEBED6xWp0BEOLkOTQFccN0FQuQu7Vj8-D9AaLqJaIzKWry4sSq_661KXO_eKz1FZ0q02T_x32h8ve3JS9X1ntNyXEnr07c2SlvQTeoamQeA0-k34pb_WSZ4rUIzIXlUz-XWt5EwlHQP4YNeDihf3-qiiU25AWyBRuBfGjs4McYhhL2uX9a1N76YrRlbiM6Owsqzn8ZAnVOoR3G-YVpIzekHamgEiQZCJG9Z25ezs7CiMnlYs5D5vNHn95uutJ4m2bj5l3CKfHxSOPOqusUNoIzkBMcjrHDFtgTq-axG-G_HYtBwqTfNskk9ZFoUBjsHU0YKu4QWNodXwWB9wVeJx_NZLxNwV