cess instead of hiding them in a database. I’ll suggest using markdown for documents like `charter.md`, `status.md`, and others, while considering reusing existing files to avoid duplication. Maybe syncing with `Vault/Clean/projects/apollo` would also work.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering documentation options**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how to address the user’s question regarding dashboards and queries later, while emphasizing that markdown in git is the best single source of truth for now. I might need to update my plan, but I want to be clear and not give a simple answer. I could offer to set it up, even though they haven't explicitly asked for it yet. It feels like a good idea to be proactive and suggest creating it right away!\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"Yes, and my strong recommendation is:\n\n**start file-first, not database-first.**\n\nFor this stage, the best persistent track is:\n\n- **Markdown as the human source of truth**\n- **JSON as the machine-readable mirror**\n- **Database only later, as a derived layer**\n\n## Why\n\n### Markdown\nBest for:\n- purpose\n- mission\n- status\n- decisions\n- deliverables\n- step checklists\n- readable continuity\n\n### JSON\nBest for:\n- structured status\n- task state\n- phase tracking\n- automation later\n\n### Database\nBest later for:\n- dashboards\n- queryable task history\n- cross-project reporting\n- automation/state engines\n\nBut if you start with “put it in the DB”, it becomes harder to read, edit, diff, and trust.\n\n---\n\n# My recommendation\n\nCreate a **canonical project control folder in the repo**, something like:\n\n```text\nprojects/\n  apollo/\n    README.md\n    charter.md\n    status.md\n    decisions.md\n    deliverables.md\n    checklist.md\n    roadmap.md\n    status.json\n```\n\n## What each file should do\n\n### `README.md`\nQuick entry point:\n- what Apollo is\n- where the important files are\n- current phase\n\n### `charter.md`\nStable purpose:\n- mission\n- scope\n- non-goals\n- core principles\n\n### `status.md`\nCurrent live state:\n- current phase\n- what is done\n- what is in progress\n- blockers\n- next actions\n\n### `decisions.md`\nArchitecture and planning decisions:\n- what was decided\n- when\n- why\n- what alternatives were rejected\n\n### `deliverables.md`\nDefines expected outputs:\n- Phase I Alpha deliverables\n- later phase deliverables\n- completion criteria\n\n### `checklist.md`\nAction-oriented execution list:\n- setup steps\n- implementation tasks\n- validation tasks\n- cleanup tasks\n\n### `roadmap.md`\nThe phased roadmap:\n- Phase I\n- Phase II\n- Phase III\n- deferred items\n\n### `status.json`\nMachine-readable state, for future automation.\n\nExample:\n```json\n{\n  \"project\": \"apollo\",\n  \"phase\": \"Phase I Alpha\",\n  \"status\": \"in_progress\",\n  \"focus\": \"standing up project-aware ingestion and grounded query loop\",\n  \"last_updated\": \"2026-04-16\",\n  \"next_actions\": [\n    \"inspect clean project docs\",\n    \"verify LightRAG input path\",\n    \"test first grounded query loop\"\n  ],\n  \"blockers\": [],\n  \"deliverables\": {\n    \"core_runtime\": \"present\",\n    \"clean_corpus\": \"present\",\n    \"query_loop\": \"not_verified\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n# Where should this live?\n\nI would **not** put the canonical version inside `Vault/Clean/`.\n\nWhy:\n- `Vault/Clean/` feels like corpus/ingestion territory\n- project governance docs should live in a stable project-management location\n- we want a distinction between:\n  - **project control docs**\n  - **knowledge corpus**\n\n## So I recommend:\n```text\nC:\\Apollo\\projects\\apollo\\\n```\n\nAnd optionally later:\n- ingest these docs into LightRAG too\n\nThat way Apollo can reason over its own project docs, but the docs are still human-owned and versioned in git.\n\n---\n\n# What about the existing files in `Vault/Clean/projects/apollo/`?\n\nThose are useful. I would treat them as:\n\n- either **seed material to promote into canonical project docs**\n- or **derived project memory**\n\nBut I would avoid maintaining two equal “official” homes forever.\n\nMy preference:\n- make `projects/apollo/` the canonical control location\n- copy/adapt the good material from `Vault/Clean/projects/apollo/`\n\n---\n\n# Best practice for consistency\n\nUse a simple rule:\n\n## Canonical rule\n- **Markdown files are the authoritative project record**\n- **JSON is generated or updated alongside them**\n- **Database mirrors state later, but does not replace the files**\n\nThat keeps the system understandable.\n\n---\n\n# If you want a minimal version\n\nWe can start even smaller:\n\n```text\nprojects/apollo/\n  charter.md\n  status.md\n  checklist.md\n  decisions.md\n  status.json\n```\n\nThat is enough to maintain continuity.\n\n---\n\n# My recommendation, concretely\n\nI would set up:\n\n```text\nprojects/apollo/\n  README.md\n  charter.md\n  status.md\n  decisions.md\n  deliverables.md\n  checklist.md\n  roadmap.md\n  status.json\n```\n\nand treat it as the **project cockpit**.\n\nThen later:\n- ingest those files into LightRAG\n- optionally sync structured parts into n8n/Postgres if useful\n\n---\n\n# Short answer to your DB question\n\n**Can we store it in a DB?** Yes.  \n**Should the DB be the primary source right now?** No.\n\nUse:\n- **MD for truth**\n- **JSON for structure**\n- **DB for later operationalization**\n\nIf you want, I can create this Apollo control folder and draft the initial files from what we’ve already established.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0143781879c152dd0169e145bba4c88191a00bc9295ce7fa32\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":8790,"output":1593,"cacheRead":54784,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65167,"cost":{"input":0.021975,"output":0.023895,"cacheRead":0.013696,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.059566}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776371117672,"responseId":"resp_0143781879c152dd0169e145aeaa8c81918b8e9b60d108abd5"}}
{"type":"message","id":"90555d44","parentId":"a95740f2","timestamp":"2026-04-16T20:29:51.953Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Thu 2026-04-16 20:29 UTC] Perfect. please create the structure as suggested. take into account this acts in two ways:\n- serving as our own tracker to maintain consistency of purpose and progress monitoring throughout the development\n- serving as a backup, in case our llm session is lost the project can be recovered inside another openclaw session directly (or handed over or parts of it handed over to another agent)\n\nso generate the files proposed containing as much information as required for this purpose. you may enhance the proposed structure if you consider it serves our purpose better"}],"timestamp":1776371391947}}
{"type":"message","id":"18c485d9","parentId":"90555d44","timestamp":"2026-04-16T20:30:02.984Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Organizing project documentation**\n\nI'm planning to read the existing Clean project docs and current files, maybe even create a status JSON. I need to be careful with the root project path, which might be /home/node/.openclaw/workspace/projects/apollo. It seems important to include a variety of documentation such as README, charter, and deliverables, focusing on backup/handover details. I should also think about enhancing the structure with files like handoff.md. Cross-referencing existing discussions and cleaned docs will be essential. I might need to inspect the root to see if the projects folder exists.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_0143781879c152dd0169e146c140008191a5c23b5a6d20d134\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp4UbL2RZ1lKZPn6a3lK7vb5MbOUOdOlfPcNtt3--5FeorhS0NHl4fjK2SKOvYrBfsyXSW-LvKLvTWsfgYnvGI1q-i4ZGvrGeHNUjkKhNFG_e3xdsg2SZVDpZHOb8EHbZ5gT3rthAfYlKQ_kqYmjIkfxGqSYZ7tn8lsy7AWqXiVu8oJsZFAOXEnu1OH7zDpTlPHz4N0215LtxBN6vR4DbM3xDaR2yvoddrwOFVadMVI27qqC84H3CUnZuA7WfGzNG6_V9Q4aMQCGgFiQMchBe3T5s2i4c2NLB8Ccd1X8uGKmHTom4nFgiTXeJLpyhSGs_kyS5HMun5cavF4dp1GcXY3GX8nnTzeA4O8QSUgTYPyJFBNwOm6wD5fxcGqx6D_x0RWx_oQEcb1IXp1nf3u7dbjGix2Da2nwemSaS7HQQGfZsSY37x9RusruvmdaFZ_lYFW6cZagtC5Eqca7ClkvwbGrH_wM-gqjh0bSsCIO2k7-661fH-3Et44kysU5iiuQ5Hq7vulEvyePLj-6YPLqTiRKeL6iMIAwt8jrWnxsPd1mErKtunQmStkxo09vGgOnbnXjZVK7hB3N0wFORnlgujxrRP26zliNbWa1FQLr4aZS-2UQKIpS9t5azA1h50SBW5HvsH5Wb930F9kU9R-H-UDSaVVW9tErp2W7xf27QxSzG4MAsidTD3kzuIHsQTPAvTZ0ltCHAjAHPxP-BCQp27_-3CF9fbvUik2mpXmvywuoJMfIpWnXNx8LRd9_-c86__vkTb5axn5eKGAIMQbLVImZM3UGN_4NI_JdlZSlo0GF96aOaCHXVJgIytfGv_5Cr2HtiJ86JtY127LRyGX22zc1xnUzA9QhSNNlOR1s_2BB9uFD-R2_OlW0ppCVwivdnCmFaiuqx9-GPnsjUnD25wdgRVVcJxy_nWiPYHEoFDxKAiPG_16BQZb5dW_dchmFAXbAI7JCb2NgP6NQGVV3FlxfSm9yFLg8P_a8vYCQWEk0w1-J95JpmUGAxMjvSqXRCIF0FC1xaJH-9TIj9YnBI3ZOS2jO9VYHXpyTyzF82qdwAcgRgu