{"type":"message","id":"74eb36df","parentId":"2a74e201","timestamp":"2026-04-16T20:43:20.061Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Finishing the missing half now. I’ll keep it compact but robust enough for recovery and handoff.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0143781879c152dd0169e149aff3908191a258611dc399a439\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_nxdGRC5AgdR6tcpXgXYpmBOT|fc_0143781879c152dd0169e149e833688191b0d64ce8e3a16eb5","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/projects/apollo/checklist.md","content":"# Apollo Checklist\n\n## Phase I Alpha checklist\n\n### A. Workspace and control layer\n- [x] Make repo root `C:\\Apollo` the active OpenClaw workspace root\n- [x] Expose the full repo to the running OpenClaw session\n- [x] Preserve the existing running stack as the basis\n- [x] Create canonical Apollo control docs under `projects/apollo/`\n- [ ] Add repo root as a safe Git directory inside the container if git operations are needed\n\n### B. Repo hygiene\n- [x] Archive the clearly legacy nested workspace content from `Intel/workspace/` into `legacy/`\n- [x] Preserve active OpenClaw runtime/config state under `Intel/`\n- [ ] Confirm any remaining legacy leftovers are either archived or intentionally retained\n- [ ] Document any directories that must never be ingested\n\n### C. Corpus validation\n- [x] Confirm `Vault/raw/` exists and contains meaningful source material\n- [x] Confirm `Vault/Clean/` contains project-level clean corpus assets\n- [ ] Inspect `Vault/Clean/ingest/ingest_manifest.json`\n- [ ] Inspect `Vault/Clean/projects/classification_refined.json`\n- [ ] Decide which subset of `Vault/Clean/` is the first retrieval surface\n- [ ] Exclude secrets or irrelevant runtime debris from retrieval\n\n### D. Retrieval validation\n- [ ] Confirm how LightRAG is currently reading `Vault/Clean`\n- [ ] Define the exact indexing / refresh path for the clean corpus\n- [ ] Verify project-scoped retrieval assumptions for Apollo vs Aurelius\n- [ ] Test the first grounded Apollo query loop\n\n### E. Validation pack\n- [ ] Create canonical test questions\n- [ ] Associate each question with expected evidence sources\n- [ ] Record baseline answers for regression testing\n\n## Current top-priority next steps\n1. inspect the clean corpus manifests and classification files\n2. verify LightRAG input and indexing behavior\n3. prove the first source-grounded query loop\n\n## Completion condition for Phase I Alpha\nApollo can answer core questions about Apollo and Aurelius from the curated corpus through the running stack, with clear grounding and recoverable project state."},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/projects/apollo/checklist.md\",\"content\":\"# Apollo Checklist\\n\\n## Phase I Alpha checklist\\n\\n### A. Workspace and control layer\\n- [x] Make repo root `C:\\\\Apollo` the active OpenClaw workspace root\\n- [x] Expose the full repo to the running OpenClaw session\\n- [x] Preserve the existing running stack as the basis\\n- [x] Create canonical Apollo control docs under `projects/apollo/`\\n- [ ] Add repo root as a safe Git directory inside the container if git operations are needed\\n\\n### B. Repo hygiene\\n- [x] Archive the clearly legacy nested workspace content from `Intel/workspace/` into `legacy/`\\n- [x] Preserve active OpenClaw runtime/config state under `Intel/`\\n- [ ] Confirm any remaining legacy leftovers are either archived or intentionally retained\\n- [ ] Document any directories that must never be ingested\\n\\n### C. Corpus validation\\n- [x] Confirm `Vault/raw/` exists and contains meaningful source material\\n- [x] Confirm `Vault/Clean/` contains project-level clean corpus assets\\n- [ ] Inspect `Vault/Clean/ingest/ingest_manifest.json`\\n- [ ] Inspect `Vault/Clean/projects/classification_refined.json`\\n- [ ] Decide which subset of `Vault/Clean/` is the first retrieval surface\\n- [ ] Exclude secrets or irrelevant runtime debris from retrieval\\n\\n### D. Retrieval validation\\n- [ ] Confirm how LightRAG is currently reading `Vault/Clean`\\n- [ ] Define the exact indexing / refresh path for the clean corpus\\n- [ ] Verify project-scoped retrieval assumptions for Apollo vs Aurelius\\n- [ ] Test the first grounded Apollo query loop\\n\\n### E. Validation pack\\n- [ ] Create canonical test questions\\n- [ ] Associate each question with expected evidence sources\\n- [ ] Record baseline answers for regression testing\\n\\n## Current top-priority next steps\\n1. inspect the clean corpus manifests and classification files\\n2. verify LightRAG input and indexing behavior\\n3. prove the first source-grounded query loop\\n\\n## Completion condition for Phase I Alpha\\nApollo can answer core questions about Apollo and Aurelius from the curated corpus through the running stack, with clear grounding and recoverable project state.\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Q8n3MpNesT2M1cSJO4INI9yb|fc_0143781879c152dd0169e149e833808191abaad9a75fc72704","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/projects/apollo/roadmap.md","content":"# Apollo Roadmap\n\n## Phase I, Foundation\n**Goal:** Apollo can reliably ingest or use curated source material, preserve project structure, retrieve relevant evidence, and support grounded querying through one governing interface.\n\n### Core concerns\n- workspace and repo clarity\n- clean project corpus\n- retrieval viability\n- project control continuity\n\n### Phase I focus in practice\nFor the current cycle, Phase I is narrower than the total vision. It is focused on:\n- using the existing running stack\n- reusing the existing `Vault/Clean/` work\n- proving the first real Apollo query loop\n\n## Phase II, Analytical Core\n**Goal:** Apollo can reason across sources rather than merely store them.\n\n### Intended additions\n- entity and claim extraction\n- relationship mapping\n- contradiction detection\n- timeline workflows\n- uncertainty-aware synthesis\n\n## Phase III, Operational Core\n**Goal:** Apollo becomes a real project/life assistant, starting with Aurelius.\n\n### Intended additions\n- regimen models\n- schedule generation\n- reminders\n- adherence tracking\n- outcome logging\n- protocol revision support\n\n## Phase IV, Program Modules\n**Goal:** Apollo becomes a host platform for specialized workflows.\n\n### Intended additions\n- Aurelius as a mature operational module\n- Remote Viewing tasking and feedback workflows\n- subliminal/pathworking generation workflows\n- module framework for future additions\n\n## Phase V, Mature Orchestration\n**Goal:** Apollo becomes a governable system of delegated intelligence.\n\n### Intended additions\n- specialist subagents where useful\n- richer task delegation\n- better observability and auditability\n- stronger local/cloud routing policy\n\n## Build order principle\nThe dependency chain should remain:\n\n**Ingestion / clean corpus -> retrieval -> grounded query loop -> analysis -> operations -> modules -> orchestration**\n\n## Anti-sprawl rule\nDo not let later-phase ideas displace the current phase proof.\nApollo advances correctly when each phase leaves behind a simpler, more reliable foundation for the next one."},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/projects/apollo/roadmap.md\",\"content\":\"# Apollo Roadmap\\n\\n## Phase I, Foundation\\n**Goal:** Apollo can reliably ingest or use curated source material, preserve project structure, retrieve relevant evidence, and support grounded querying through one governing interface.\\n\\n### Core concerns\\n- workspace and repo clarity\\n- clean project corpus\\n- retrieval viability\\n- project control continuity\\n\\n### Phase I focus in practice\\nFor the current cycle, Phase I is narrower than the total vision. It is focused on:\\n- using the existing running stack\\n- reusing the existing `Vault/Clean/` work\\n- proving the first real Apollo query loop\\n\\n## Phase II, Analytical Core\\n**Goal:** Apollo can reason across sources rather than merely store them.\\n\\n### Intended additions\\n- entity and claim extraction\\n- relationship mapping\\n- contradiction detection\\n- timeline workflows\\n- uncertainty-aware synthesis\\n\\n## Phase III, Operational Core\\n**Goal:** Apollo becomes a real project/life assistant, starting with Aurelius.\\n\\n### Intended additions\\n- regimen models\\n- schedule generation\\n- reminders\\n- adherence tracking\\n- outcome logging\\n- protocol revision support\\n\\n## Phase IV, Program Modules\\n**Goal:** Apollo becomes a host platform for specialized workflows.\\n\\n### Intended additions\\n- Aurelius as a mature operational module\\n- Remote Viewing tasking and feedback workflows\\n- subliminal/pathworking generation workflows\\n- module framework for future additions\\n\\n## Phase V, Mature Orchestration\\n**Goal:** Apollo becomes a governable system of delegated intelligence.\\n\\n### Intended additions\\n- specialist subagents where useful\\n- richer task delegation\\n- better observability and auditability\\n- stronger local/cloud routing policy\\n\\n## Build order principle\\nThe dependency chain should remain:\\n\\n**Ingestion / clean corpus -> retrieval -> grounded query loop -> analysis -> operations -> modules -> orchestration**\\n\\n## Anti-sprawl rule\\nDo not let later-phase ideas displace the current phase proof.\\nApollo advances correctly when each phase leaves behind a simpler, more reliable foundation for the next one.\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Lgop0trzibalEH3ODRuZj0GF|fc_0143781879c152dd0169e149e833948191b15f4e9aa2eb3f2a","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/projects/apollo/architecture.md","content":"# Apollo Architecture\n\n## Text-form component diagram\n\n```text\n                                  [ ADMINISTRATOR / OPERATOR ]\n                                              |\n                                              v\n                                  [ APOLLO ADMIN INTERFACE ]\n                               (single governing interaction point)\n                                              |\n                                              v\n                                [ OPENCLAW ORCHESTRATION CORE ]\n                         task typing | routing | policy | execution control\n                           project scope | tool use | agent coordination\n                                              |\n                  ----------------------------------------------------------------\n                  |                         |                         |            |\n                  v                         v                         v            v\n        [ INGESTION CONTROL ]     [ QUERY / ANALYSIS CONTROL ]   [ DEV CONTROL ] [ MODULE CONTROL ]\n      intake routing, queues,      retrieval orchestration,       optional        project modules:\n      processing state, retries    synthesis, evidence bundling   later           Aurelius, RV, etc.\n                  |                         |\n                  v                         v\n      ------------------------      ------------------------\n      |          |         |        |          |          |\n      v          v         v        v          v          v\n [TEXT PATH] [OCR PATH] [WEB/MEDIA] [LightRAG] [MODEL RT] [MEMORY]\n                        EXTRACTION                         LAYERS\n      |          |         |        |          |          |\n      ------------------------      ------------------------\n                  |                         |\n                  v                         v\n                [ NORMALIZATION / CANONICAL ARTIFACT LAYER ]\n         source record | raw artifact | extracted artifact | normalized artifact\n                  provenance | project binding | metadata | structure | confidence\n                                              |\n                                              v\n                              [ STORAGE AND KNOWLEDGE SUBSTRATE ]\n                 -----------------------------------------------------------\n                 |                         |                              |\n                 v                         v                              v\n          [ RAW ARTIFACT STORE ]   [ METADATA / REGISTRY ]       [ INDEX / RETRIEVAL STORE ]\n         originals, captures,      project registry, source      LightRAG structures,\n         snapshots, media          registry, processing status   retrieval units, links\n                                              |\n                                              v\n                                   [ RESPONSE / ACTION OUTPUTS ]\n                         grounded answers | summaries | reports | task proposals\n```\n\n## Responsibility boundaries\n### OpenClaw\nOwns orchestration, task routing, tool use, project scope, and session execution.\n\n### Open WebUI\nOwns the human-facing interaction surface.\n\n### LightRAG\nOwns retrieval structures and evidence recall over the curated corpus.\n\n### Vault/Clean\nActs as the current clean corpus and evidence-preparation layer.\n\n### projects/apollo\nActs as the canonical control layer for mission, progress, and handoff.\n\n## Current architectural stance\nFor now Apollo should remain thin:\n- one admin interface\n- one curated corpus path\n- one retrieval layer\n- one query loop\n\nComplex agent orchestration is deferred until this foundation is proven."},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/projects/apollo/architecture.md\",\"content\":\"# Apollo Architecture\\n\\n## Text-form component diagram\\n\\n```text\\n                                  [ ADMINISTRATOR / OPERATOR ]\\n                                              |\\n                                              v\\n                                  [ APOLLO ADMIN INTERFACE ]\\n                               (single governing interaction point)\\n                                              |\\n                                              v\\n                                [ OPENCLAW ORCHESTRATION CORE ]\\n                         task typing | routing | policy | execution control\\n                           project scope | tool use | agent coordination\\n                                              |\\n                  ----------------------------------------------------------------\\n                  |                         |                         |            |\\n                  v                         v                         v            v\\n        [ INGESTION CONTROL ]     [ QUERY / ANALYSIS CONTROL ]   [ DEV CONTROL ] [ MODULE CONTROL ]\\n      intake routing, queues,      retrieval orchestration,       optional        project modules:\\n      processing state, retries    synthesis, evidence bundling   later           Aurelius, RV, etc.\\n                  |                         |\\n                  v                         v\\n      ------------------------      ------------------------\\n      |          |         |        |          |          |\\n      v          v         v        v          v          v\\n [TEXT PATH] [OCR PATH] [WEB/MEDIA] [LightRAG] [MODEL RT] [MEMORY]\\n                        EXTRACTION                         LAYERS\\n      |          |         |        |          |          |\\n      ------------------------      ------------------------\\n                  |                         |\\n                  v                         v\\n                [ NORMALIZATION / CANONICAL ARTIFACT LAYER ]\\n         source record | raw artifact | extracted artifact | normalized artifact\\n                  provenance | project binding | metadata | structure | confidence\\n                                              |\\n                                              v\\n                              [ STORAGE AND KNOWLEDGE SUBSTRATE ]\\n                 -----------------------------------------------------------\\n                 |                         |                              |\\n                 v                         v                              v\\n          [ RAW ARTIFACT STORE ]   [ METADATA / REGISTRY ]       [ INDEX / RETRIEVAL STORE ]\\n         originals, captures,      project registry, source      LightRAG structures,\\n         snapshots, media          registry, processing status   retrieval units, links\\n                                              |\\n                                              v\\n                                   [ RESPONSE / ACTION OUTPUTS ]\\n                         grounded answers | summaries | reports | task proposals\\n```\\n\\n## Responsibility boundaries\\n### OpenClaw\\nOwns orchestration, task routing, tool use, project scope, and session execution.\\n\\n### Open WebUI\\nOwns the human-facing interaction surface.\\n\\n### LightRAG\\nOwns retrieval structures and evidence recall over the curated corpus.\\n\\n### Vault/Clean\\nActs as the current clean corpus and evidence-preparation layer.\\n\\n### projects/apollo\\nActs as the canonical control layer for mission, progress, and handoff.\\n\\n## Current architectural stance\\nFor now Apollo should remain thin:\\n- one admin interface\\n- one curated corpus path\\n- one retrieval layer\\n- one query loop\\n\\nComplex agent orchestration is deferred until this foundation is proven.\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9ugsr0o0NCzy8XrrNlG8uVEX|fc_0143781879c152dd0169e149e833a481919d3b1234c32c42f5","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/projects/apollo/handoff.md","content":"# Apollo Handoff Notes\n\n## Purpose of this file\nThis file is for session recovery and handoff to another OpenClaw session or another agent.\n\n## If you are a new session or new agent\nStart here:\n1. read `projects/apollo/README.md`\n2. read `charter.md`\n3. read `status.md`\n4. read `checklist.md`\n5. read `decisions.md`\n6. inspect `Vault/Clean/projects/apollo/` and `Vault/Clean/projects/aurelius/`\n7. inspect `Vault/Clean/ingest/` and `Vault/Clean/reports/`\n8. confirm the running stack still includes OpenClaw, Ollama, Open WebUI, and LightRAG\n\n## Current project situation\nApollo is in a planning-to-technical-transition stage.\nThe stack is already running.\nThe repo root is now the workspace root.\nThe project already has a useful clean corpus under `Vault/Clean/`.\nThe immediate aim is not advanced orchestration but proving a grounded retrieval/query loop for Apollo and Aurelius planning material.\n\n## High-value facts\n- The user wants one governing assistant, not one monolith\n- The system should be local-first and modular\n- `Vault/Clean/` contains prior ingestion/digestion work and should be reused\n- `projects/apollo/` is now the canonical project control surface\n- Legacy nested workspace clutter from `Intel/workspace/` has been archived under `legacy/`\n\n## Next best actions\n- inspect the clean corpus manifests and classification files\n- verify LightRAG input/index behavior against the clean corpus\n- define or verify the first retrieval surface\n- prove the first grounded query loop\n\n## Warning notes\n- Do not casually ingest secrets or irrelevant runtime files\n- Do not reintroduce heavy orchestration before the thin backbone works\n- Keep Apollo control docs and corpus docs conceptually separate\n\n## Handoff standard\nAny major new decision or milestone should update at least:\n- `status.md`\n- `decisions.md`\n- `checklist.md`\n- `status.json`\n\nIf a larger shift occurs, also update:\n- `charter.md`\n- `roadmap.md`\n- `deliverables.md`"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/projects/apollo/handoff.md\",\"content\":\"# Apollo Handoff Notes\\n\\n## Purpose of this file\\nThis file is for session recovery and handoff to another OpenClaw session or another agent.\\n\\n## If you are a new session or new agent\\nStart here:\\n1. read `projects/apollo/README.md`\\n2. read `charter.md`\\n3. read `status.md`\\n4. read `checklist.md`\\n5. read `decisions.md`\\n6. inspect `Vault/Clean/projects/apollo/` and `Vault/Clean/projects/aurelius/`\\n7. inspect `Vault/Clean/ingest/` and `Vault/Clean/reports/`\\n8. confirm the running stack still includes OpenClaw, Ollama, Open WebUI, and LightRAG\\n\\n## Current project situation\\nApollo is in a planning-to-technical-transition stage.\\nThe stack is already running.\\nThe repo root is now the workspace root.\\nThe project already has a useful clean corpus under `Vault/Clean/`.\\nThe immediate aim is not advanced orchestration but proving a grounded retrieval/query loop for Apollo and Aurelius planning material.\\n\\n## High-value facts\\n- The user wants one governing assistant, not one monolith\\n- The system should be local-first and modular\\n- `Vault/Clean/` contains prior ingestion/digestion work and should be reused\\n- `projects/apollo/` is now the canonical project control surface\\n- Legacy nested workspace clutter from `Intel/workspace/` has been archived under `legacy/`\\n\\n## Next best actions\\n- inspect the clean corpus manifests and classification files\\n- verify LightRAG input/index behavior against the clean corpus\\n- define or verify the first retrieval surface\\n- prove the first grounded query loop\\n\\n## Warning notes\\n- Do not casually ingest secrets or irrelevant runtime files\\n- Do not reintroduce heavy orchestration before the thin backbone works\\n- Keep Apollo control docs and corpus docs conceptually separate\\n\\n## Handoff standard\\nAny major new decision or milestone should update at least:\\n- `status.md`\\n- `decisions.md`\\n- `checklist.md`\\n- `status.json`\\n\\nIf a larger shift occurs, also update:\\n- `charter.md`\\n- `roadmap.md`\\n- `deliverables.md`\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_MWhEHKWEgxzAmYTkf63kOszg|fc_0143781879c152dd0169e149e833ac819185500435058a92d6","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/projects/apollo/sources.md","content":"# Apollo Sources\n\n## Purpose\nThis file records where the canonical Apollo control docs were derived from, so future sessions can trace the origin of the current project record.\n\n## Primary source groups\n\n### 1. Current planning conversation\nThe current OpenClaw session established:\n- the formal tasking map\n- the capability matrix\n- the phased roadmap\n- the Phase I Alpha implementation blueprint\n- the decision to keep the stack thin for now\n- the decision to create `projects/apollo/` as the canonical control folder\n\n### 2. Existing distilled Apollo docs\nSource path:\n- `Vault/Clean/projects/apollo/`\n\nFiles consulted:\n- `master_context.md`\n- `timeline.md`\n- `decisions.md`\n- `tasks.md`\n- `deliverables.md`\n\n### 3. Existing clean corpus support material\nRelevant supporting paths:\n- `Vault/Clean/conversation_slices/`\n- `Vault/Clean/ingest/`\n- `Vault/Clean/reports/`\n- `Vault/Clean/projects/`\n\n### 4. Existing raw corpus\nSource path:\n- `Vault/raw/`\n\nThis contains Apollo and Aurelius source material and remains the deeper evidence/archive layer.\n\n### 5. Existing repo/runtime structure\nObserved paths:\n- `docker-compose.yaml`\n- `Intel/`\n- `Vault/`\n- `data/`\n- `legacy/`\n\n## Source usage rule\nWhen updating Apollo control docs:\n- prefer canonical control docs first\n- then supporting clean corpus docs\n- then raw source material when a deeper check is needed\n\n## Important distinction\n- `projects/apollo/` = canonical control and continuity layer\n- `Vault/Clean/` = curated knowledge/corpus layer\n- `Vault/raw/` = raw evidence/archive layer"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/projects/apollo/sources.md\",\"content\":\"# Apollo Sources\\n\\n## Purpose\\nThis file records where the canonical Apollo control docs were derived from, so future sessions can trace the origin of the current project record.\\n\\n## Primary source groups\\n\\n### 1. Current planning conversation\\nThe current OpenClaw session established:\\n- the formal tasking map\\n- the capability matrix\\n- the phased roadmap\\n- the Phase I Alpha implementation blueprint\\n- the decision to keep the stack thin for now\\n- the decision to create `projects/apollo/` as the canonical control folder\\n\\n### 2. Existing distilled Apollo docs\\nSource path:\\n- `Vault/Clean/projects/apollo/`\\n\\nFiles consulted:\\n- `master_context.md`\\n- `timeline.md`\\n- `decisions.md`\\n- `tasks.md`\\n- `deliverables.md`\\n\\n### 3. Existing clean corpus support material\\nRelevant supporting paths:\\n- `Vault/Clean/conversation_slices/`\\n- `Vault/Clean/ingest/`\\n- `Vault/Clean/reports/`\\n- `Vault/Clean/projects/`\\n\\n### 4. Existing raw corpus\\nSource path:\\n- `Vault/raw/`\\n\\nThis contains Apollo and Aurelius source material and remains the deeper evidence/archive layer.\\n\\n### 5. Existing repo/runtime structure\\nObserved paths:\\n- `docker-compose.yaml`\\n- `Intel/`\\n- `Vault/`\\n- `data/`\\n- `legacy/`\\n\\n## Source usage rule\\nWhen updating Apollo control docs:\\n- prefer canonical control docs first\\n- then supporting clean corpus docs\\n- then raw source material when a deeper check is needed\\n\\n## Important distinction\\n- `projects/apollo/` = canonical control and continuity layer\\n- `Vault/Clean/` = curated knowledge/corpus layer\\n- `Vault/raw/` = raw evidence/archive layer\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_aKWRx8iXoeuHhsO1E2IhHhV2|fc_0143781879c152dd0169e149e833b88191a4cfa47a4fbfe6cd","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/projects/apollo/status.json","content":"{\n  \"project\": \"apollo\",\n  \"date\": \"2026-04-16\",\n  \"overall_status\": \"in_progress\",\n  \"active_phase\": \"Phase I Alpha\",\n  \"focus\": \"Establish a thin but real Apollo backbone using the existing running stack and the existing clean Apollo/Aurelius corpus, then prove the first grounded retrieval/query loop.\",\n  \"principles\": [\n    \"one governing assistant, not one monolith\",\n    \"local-first, cloud-augmented only when justified\",\n    \"OTS-first, custom where needed\",\n    \"backbone before theatrics\",\n    \"markdown is the primary project record\",\n    \"preserve provenance and project boundaries\"\n  ],\n  \"current_assets\": {\n    \"running_stack\": true,\n    \"full_repo_visible_in_workspace\": true,\n    \"clean_corpus_present\": true,\n    \"legacy_nested_workspace_archived\": true,\n    \"canonical_project_control_folder_present\": true\n  },\n  \"next_actions\": [\n    \"inspect Vault/Clean ingest and classification manifests\",\n    \"verify LightRAG input and indexing behavior\",\n    \"define the first retrieval surface\",\n    \"prove the first grounded Apollo query loop\",\n    \"create a validation pack of canonical project questions\"\n  ],\n  \"blockers\": [\n    \"Git safe.directory issue inside container if repo operations are needed\",\n    \"LightRAG end-to-end indexing behavior against the clean corpus not yet verified\"\n  ],\n  \"control_files\": [\n    \"README.md\",\n    \"charter.md\",\n    \"status.md\",\n    \"decisions.md\",\n    \"deliverables.md\",\n    \"checklist.md\",\n    \"roadmap.md\",\n    \"architecture.md\",\n    \"handoff.md\",\n    \"sources.md\",\n    \"status.json\"\n  ],\n  \"key_paths\": {\n    \"project_control\": \"projects/apollo\",\n    \"clean_corpus\": \"Vault/Clean\",\n    \"raw_corpus\": \"Vault/raw\",\n    \"retrieval_db\": \"Vault/Database\",\n    \"runtime_state\": \"Intel\",\n    \"legacy_archive\": \"legacy\"\n  }\n}"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/projects/apollo/status.json\",\"content\":\"{\\n  \\\"project\\\": \\\"apollo\\\",\\n  \\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-04-16\\\",\\n  \\\"overall_status\\\": \\\"in_progress\\\",\\n  \\\"active_phase\\\": \\\"Phase I Alpha\\\",\\n  \\\"focus\\\": \\\"Establish a thin but real Apollo backbone using the existing running stack and the existing clean Apollo/Aurelius corpus, then prove the first grounded retrieval/query loop.\\\",\\n  \\\"principles\\\": [\\n    \\\"one governing assistant, not one monolith\\\",\\n    \\\"local-first, cloud-augmented only when justified\\\",\\n    \\\"OTS-first, custom where needed\\\",\\n    \\\"backbone before theatrics\\\",\\n    \\\"markdown is the primary project record\\\",\\n    \\\"preserve provenance and project boundaries\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"current_assets\\\": {\\n    \\\"running_stack\\\": true,\\n    \\\"full_repo_visible_in_workspace\\\": true,\\n    \\\"clean_corpus_present\\\": true,\\n    \\\"legacy_nested_workspace_archived\\\": true,\\n    \\\"canonical_project_control_folder_present\\\": true\\n  },\\n  \\\"next_actions\\\": [\\n    \\\"inspect Vault/Clean ingest and classification manifests\\\",\\n    \\\"verify LightRAG input and indexing behavior\\\",\\n    \\\"define the first retrieval surface\\\",\\n    \\\"prove the first grounded Apollo query loop\\\",\\n    \\\"create a validation pack of canonical project questions\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"blockers\\\": [\\n    \\\"Git safe.directory issue inside container if repo operations are needed\\\",\\n    \\\"LightRAG end-to-end indexing behavior against the clean corpus not yet verified\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"control_files\\\": [\\n    \\\"README.md\\\",\\n    \\\"charter.md\\\",\\n    \\\"status.md\\\",\\n    \\\"decisions.md\\\",\\n    \\\"deliverables.md\\\",\\n    \\\"checklist.md\\\",\\n    \\\"roadmap.md\\\",\\n    \\\"architecture.md\\\",\\n    \\\"handoff.md\\\",\\n    \\\"sources.md\\\",\\n    \\\"status.json\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"key_paths\\\": {\\n    \\\"project_control\\\": \\\"projects/apollo\\\",\\n    \\\"clean_corpus\\\": \\\"Vault/Clean\\\",\\n    \\\"raw_corpus\\\": \\\"Vault/raw\\\",\\n    \\\"retrieval_db\\\": \\\"Vault/Database\\\",\\n    \\\"runtime_state\\\": \\\"Intel\\\",\\n    \\\"legacy_archive\\\": \\\"legacy\\\"\\n  }\\n}\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":12