ects/apollo/` and adding a lightweight pointer in AGENTS or HEARTBEAT. Including a permanent directive in `AGENTS.md` could help streamline future sessions regarding Apollo.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying project context**\\n\\nIt looks like AGENTS.md is always included in the project context, which is good. I should add a lightweight instruction to AGENTS, but I’m debating whether to update HEARTBEAT as well—maybe not. Creating a `MEMORY.md` for long-term distillation could be useful, but for direct missions, AGENTS is the best spot for this. I wonder about using `openclaw.json` for custom system prompts, but instructions might not be accessible in that context. I need to stay focused on the current setup.\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"Yes, absolutely, but the **right way is not to stuff the whole project into the agent mission**.\n\n## Best approach inside OpenClaw\n\n### 1. Keep the real project memory in files\nYou already have the right structure now:\n\n- `projects/apollo/...`\n\nThat should remain the canonical source.\n\n### 2. Add a **small permanent instruction** to OpenClaw\nBest place:\n\n- root `AGENTS.md`\n\nWe can add something like:\n\n- when the user is working on Apollo, treat `projects/apollo/` as the canonical control folder\n- read `README.md`, `status.md`, `checklist.md`, `decisions.md`, and `handoff.md` before major Apollo work\n- update those files when major decisions or progress occur\n\nThat gives future sessions a standing mission rule.\n\n## What I recommend against\nDo **not**:\n- paste the entire project state into the agent mission\n- overload `SOUL.md` with project mechanics\n- rely only on chat memory\n\nThat gets brittle fast.\n\n## Best layering\n\n### Persistent mission rule\nPut in `AGENTS.md`:\n- where Apollo control docs live\n- when to read them\n- when to update them\n\n### Project knowledge\nKeep in:\n- `projects/apollo/`\n\n### Curated evidence/corpus\nKeep in:\n- `Vault/Clean/`\n\n### Long-term distilled memory\nOptionally later:\n- `MEMORY.md`\n\n## Short answer\n**Yes, we can program this into the OpenClaw instance, and the cleanest method is to add a lightweight Apollo operating rule to `AGENTS.md`, not to bloat the core mission.**\n\nIf you want, I can make that edit now.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0143781879c152dd0169e14a423d308191a7fdb9d2dc74935a\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":238,"output":876,"cacheRead":83840,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":84954,"cost":{"input":0.000595,"output":0.01314,"cacheRead":0.02096,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.034695000000000004}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776372277159,"responseId":"resp_0143781879c152dd0169e14a36466081918bc54d5bcec43904"}}
